all in one place?

45:02.741 --> 45:07.579
As you know,
       today is our very first

45:07.621 --> 45:10.708
all-female press conference.

45:15.295 --> 45:19.925
And the first of what I hope
     is many, many more to come.

45:19.967 --> 45:22.428
I have been given a directive

45:22.469 --> 45:27.266
that the topics we discuss
    while we're all here together

45:27.307 --> 45:32.312
must stay on the subject
         of women's things.

45:32.354 --> 45:37.443
So, cleaning,
      baking all come to mind.

45:37.484 --> 45:41.739
But today, with these
       trying times before us,

45:41.780 --> 45:46.201
many more women are finding
      work outside of the home.

45:46.243 --> 45:49.997
And it becomes
      that much more difficult

45:50.038 --> 45:53.542
to find time to prepare meals

45:53.584 --> 45:55.753
for our families.

45:55.794 --> 45:59.465
And so, I am passing around

45:59.506 --> 46:02.259
a quick and easy recipe

46:02.301 --> 46:05.012
that will only take 30 minutes,

46:05.053 --> 46:07.514
that costs just a few cents,

46:07.556 --> 46:10.267
and that feeds a family of four.

46:10.309 --> 46:13.103
That way, your readers

46:13.145 --> 46:15.981
will be able
       to have plenty of time

46:16.023 --> 46:20.652
to educate themselves about
 what's happening in our country.

46:20.694 --> 46:23.781
-Yes!

46:24.406 --> 46:28.994
Now, women's suffrage has been
     secured for some time now,

46:29.036 --> 46:31.205
but many women, I'm afraid,

46:31.246 --> 46:34.333
still act as if
       it's purely ceremonial.

46:34.374 --> 46:35.918
Now, don't get me wrong,

46:35.959 --> 46:38.837
it is prudent to vote

46:38.879 --> 46:41.507
alongside your husbands.

46:41.548 --> 46:46.178
But voting only
      on your husband's beliefs

46:46.220 --> 46:49.973
puts your own beliefs
         out of the picture.

46:51.183 --> 46:55.729
We have the right to vote,
         but we must use it.

46:56.230 --> 47:01.151
The educated woman
 is the woman of the future.

47:01.193 --> 47:02.319
Yes!

47:07.115 --> 47:11.578
Well, if you'd like to ask
      some questions, I'm open.

47:11.620 --> 47:14.081
-Ms. Hickok.

47:14.122 --> 47:17.042
Thank you, Madam First Lady.

47:17.084 --> 47:18.836
What's your recipe

47:18.877 --> 47:21.630
for basic labor regulations
            in industries

47:21.672 --> 47:24.967
populated largely by women?
        The garment industry?

47:25.008 --> 47:28.053
Ooh, that is
        a very good question.

47:28.095 --> 47:31.223
Well, I would say,

47:31.265 --> 47:34.726
my very first ingredient...

47:37.271 --> 47:40.232
...is a senator
         in North Carolina.

47:40.274 --> 47:43.110
-Uh-uh, uh-uh!

47:50.617 --> 47:53.328
Oh, she's hungry!
           I'm hungry too.

47:57.082 --> 47:58.750
Let's go to the Russians.

47:58.792 --> 48:00.544
Olga with the eyebrow
         is singing tonight.

48:00.586 --> 48:03.881
-Is she?   J'adore   Olga.
           -Petra's it is.

48:14.975 --> 48:17.394
Oh, the fun
     is just beginning, ladies.

48:17.436 --> 48:18.353
Viens-tu?

48:20.022 --> 48:22.357
Ooh. Yes.

48:23.442 --> 48:25.611
I was just taking
         a moment to imagine

48:25.652 --> 48:30.073
what it might be like to live
     like this all of the time.

48:31.325 --> 48:32.534
Happy.

48:34.995 --> 48:36.413
Yes.

48:38.582 --> 48:41.043
I've been meaning to ask you.
             I have to--

48:42.044 --> 48:43.962
I have to speak next week
             at Barnard,

48:44.004 --> 48:45.714
and I've never actually...

48:47.424 --> 48:48.550
How do you do it?

48:49.551 --> 48:52.346
Oh, is Hick afraid
         of public speaking?

48:52.387 --> 48:53.972
She's terrified.

48:54.014 --> 48:58.101
Well, the truth is,
         I'm terrified too.

48:58.143 --> 48:59.937
-No, I don't believe it.
           -No, it's true.

48:59.978 --> 49:01.730
-I don't.
            -It is true.

49:03.148 --> 49:04.691
But it gets better.

49:08.362 --> 49:11.990
Sometimes, what one needs to say

49:12.032 --> 49:15.243
is too important
     to let fear get in the way.

49:25.045 --> 49:27.798
But the best piece of advice
             I ever got

49:27.839 --> 49:31.718
was from Louis Howe, who said...

49:34.388 --> 49:36.598
"If you've got something to say,

49:37.474 --> 49:39.685
say it and sit down."

49:51.279 --> 49:54.157
pensive music

50:09.339 --> 50:11.925
"Dear Mrs. Ford,
      I am writing to tell you

50:11.967 --> 50:14.094
that because of your bravery
   I was able to have the courage

50:14.136 --> 50:15.846
to have a mammogram.

50:15.887 --> 50:18.598
Luckily, I had a good test
        and negative results,

50:18.640 --> 50:21.685
but it has inspired me to start
 a program to get people involved

50:21.727 --> 50:24.271
and get this important issue
        up-front and center.

50:24.312 --> 50:25.856
Thanks again. Peggy."

50:25.897 --> 50:27.941
"Dear Mrs. Ford,
          thank you so much

50:27.983 --> 50:30.110
for making people aware
          of breast cancer

50:30.152 --> 50:31.611
and how to detect it.

50:31.653 --> 50:33.321
My mother and I
         are both scheduled

50:33.363 --> 50:35.115
to have mammograms next week."

50:35.157 --> 50:37.617
"Dear Mrs. Ford,
    I wanted to write you a note

50:37.659 --> 50:39.786
and thank you
    for your bravery and honesty

50:39.828 --> 50:41.204
during what I imagine to be

50:41.246 --> 50:42.831
a very difficult
        and frightening time

50:42.873 --> 50:44.332
for you and your family."

50:44.374 --> 50:45.876
"I am hoping you are
           feeling better

50:45.917 --> 50:47.711
and that your family members
           and loved ones

50:47.753 --> 50:49.337
are safe and sound.

50:49.379 --> 50:51.840
Thank you for your bravery
          and your ability

50:51.882 --> 50:53.383
to face something so difficult

50:53.425 --> 50:55.969
with such style and grace."

50:56.011 --> 50:58.055
pensive music

51:41.223 --> 51:43.266
music intensifies

51:50.273 --> 51:51.316
Betty?

51:57.364 --> 51:58.573
Hey.

52:29.271 --> 52:30.647
You're beautiful.

52:35.777 --> 52:36.820
You hear me?

